attributes.Long form description: The student grabs the new battery and the GoPro. The student inspects the GoPro looking for the battery slot and the instructor tells him it is on the right side of the GoPro. The student puts the new battery back on the table and proceeds to open the battery slot door. The student removes the old battery from the GoPro, puts it on the table and then, grabs the new battery and inserts it in the battery slot of the GoPro. The student closes the battery slot door and puts the GoPro on the table. The student grabs the GoPro and looks for the Sd card slot but does not find it. The instructor tells him that the Sd card slot is located in the battery slot of the GoPro. The student opens the battery slot door, inspects it and proceeds to remove the old Sd card from the GoPro. After placing the old Sd card on the table, the student grabs the new Sd card, inserts it in the corresponding slot and struggles to attach it. The instructor recommends removing the battery first, but the student manages to attach the Sd card without doing it. The student closes the battery slot door. The student inspects the GoPro looking for the power button and the instructor tells him it is located on its left side. The student presses the power button and turns on the GoPro. The student presses the power button again but fails to turn off the GoPro. The student presses the power button again but, this time, keeps it hold for a couple of seconds and turns off the GoPro. The student grabs the strap from the table, inspects it and the instructor tells him to first remove the lock screw from the strap. The student places the GoPro on the table and proceeds to unscrew the lock screw. The student grabs the GoPro, inspects it and then releases the mount. The student assembles the GoPro on the strap and screws the lock screw to attach it. The student places the GoPro with the strap on the table. The student grabs the GoPro, unscrews the lock screw and removes the strap from the GoPro. The student places the strap on the table, grabs the handheld grip, inspects it and also places the lock screw from the strap on the table. The student tries to assemble the GoPro on the handheld grip but realizes that he needs to remove the lock screw first. The student removes the lock screw from the handheld grip, assembles the GoPro and places them on the table to be able to screw the lock screw back. The student struggles but finally manages to screw the lock screw. The student removes the lock screw, places it on the table and disassembles the GoPro from the handheld grip. The student places both the GoPro and handheld grip on the table.
